After learning of the death of popular award-winning hip-hop rapper Rikhado Muziwendlovu Makhado, 34, popularly known as Riky Rick, fans and members of the music industry took to social media to pay their heartfelt tributes. He was also known by several other names, including Boss Zonke, Master Makhado, Minister of Energy, and King Kotini. He rose to mainstream fame with his platinum-certified album Family Values in 2015 after making a name for himself and asserting his influence in South Africa's hip-hop culture for quite some time behind the scenes. His greatest hits include Amantombazane, Boss Zonke, and Sidlukotini. The Makhado family have requested privacy during this period.